---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import TimeViolenceCalculator from '../../components/calculators/TimeViolenceCalculator.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Time Violence Score Calculator" description="Calculate Time Violence Score for any system">
  <article class="content">
    <header>
      <h1>Time Violence Score Calculator</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: var(--league-gray); margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">
        Calculate how much time a system consumes beyond necessity
      </p>
    </header>
    
    <TimeViolenceCalculator />
    
    <section style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl); padding: var(--spacing-lg); background-color: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 5px;">
      <h2>Understanding Time Violence</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Time Violence</strong> occurs whenever a process, policy, or interface consumes more human time than is operationally or informationally necessary.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Time Violence Score combines two sources of waste:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Operational Latency</strong>: Time lost to procedure — queues, delays, forms, redundancies</li>
        <li><strong>Informational Distortion</strong>: Time lost to uncertainty, confusion, or opacity (0-1 scale)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Every hospital queue, bureaucratic delay, or opaque algorithm registers a positive TV(S). When that score exceeds the threshold of necessity, the system becomes predatory.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/chapters/chapter-01">Read more in Chapter 1 →</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

